OL,4,CGrenfell: Government defeated on fire
OL,5,Csafety costs bill
OL,6, The government has been defeated for a
OL,7, fourth time on its Fire Safety Bill as
OL,8, the House of Lords voted to shield
OL,9, residents from fire safety work costs.
OL,11,FMPs had, earlier in the day, rejected
OL,12,Fthe Lords amendment but it will now be
OL,13,Freinserted into the bill.
OL,15,FThousands of leaseholders are currently
OL,16,Ffacing large bills to pay for safety
OL,17,Fimprovements following the Grenfell
OL,18,Ffire which killed 72 people.
OL,20,FHousing minister Chris Pincher said the
OL,21,FLords' amendment was "ineffective".
